  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-03-18",
    "date": "2022-01-18T20:36:43Z",
    "text": "This bill expands eligibility for Post-9/11 GI Bill benefits to members of the National Guard who perform certain full-time service at the request of the President or the Secretary of Defense (i.e., full-time National Guard duty). Specifically, the bill eliminates the existing requirement that eligible full-time service must be in response to a declared national emergency. The bill also specifies that training is not included as full-time service for purposes of eligibility for these members."
  },
